11#include "rtc_base/unique_id_generator.h"
12
13#include <limits>
14#include <vector>
15
16#include "rtc_base/helpers.h"
17#include "rtc_base/string_encode.h"
18#include "rtc_base/string_to_number.h"

20namespace rtc {
21
22UniqueRandomIdGenerator::UniqueRandomIdGenerator() : known_ids_() {}
23UniqueRandomIdGenerator::UniqueRandomIdGenerator(ArrayView<uint32_t> known_ids)
24 : known_ids_(known_ids.begin(), known_ids.end()) {}
25
26UniqueRandomIdGenerator::~UniqueRandomIdGenerator() = default;
27
28uint32_t UniqueRandomIdGenerator::GenerateId() {
29 webrtc::MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
30
31 RTC_CHECK_LT(known_ids_.size(), std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max() - 1);
32 while (true) {
33 auto pair = known_ids_.insert(CreateRandomNonZeroId());
34 if (pair.second) {
35 return *pair.first;
36 }
37 }
38}
39
40bool UniqueRandomIdGenerator::AddKnownId(uint32_t value) {
41 webrtc::MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
42 return known_ids_.insert(value).second;
43}
44
45UniqueStringGenerator::UniqueStringGenerator() : unique_number_generator_() {}
46UniqueStringGenerator::UniqueStringGenerator(ArrayView<std::string> known_ids) {
47 for (const std::string& str : known_ids) {
48 AddKnownId(str);
49 }
50}
51
52UniqueStringGenerator::~UniqueStringGenerator() = default;
53
54std::string UniqueStringGenerator::GenerateString() {
55 return ToString(unique_number_generator_.GenerateNumber());
56}
57
58bool UniqueStringGenerator::AddKnownId(const std::string& value) {
59 absl::optional<uint32_t> int_value = StringToNumber<uint32_t>(value);
60 // The underlying generator works for uint32_t values, so if the provided
61 // value is not a uint32_t it will never be generated anyway.
62 if (int_value.has_value()) {
63 return unique_number_generator_.AddKnownId(int_value.value());
64 }
65 return false;
66}
